# HushNote Ukrainian glossary (issue #8)
# Copy to `glossary.uk.txt` to activate:  cp glossary.uk.txt.example glossary.uk.txt
#
# Format: one rule per line as  pattern => replacement
#   - lines starting with '#' are comments; blank lines are ignored
#   - the left side may list phonetic variants separated by '|'
#   - matching is case-insensitive (Cyrillic-aware) and whole-word
#
# These entries normalize common phonetic Cyrillic renderings of English tech
# terms back to their canonical English spelling. Tailor them to your stack.
#
# CAUTION: only map unambiguous, multi-letter phonetic renderings. Do NOT map
# short words that also exist in ordinary speech — matching is whole-word, so a
# rule like `под => pod` would rewrite the everyday preposition "под" ("под
# нагрузкою") and corrupt normal sentences. If you must catch Kubernetes "pod",
# use a distinctive phrase (e.g. `к8с под => k8s pod`) rather than the bare word.
кубернетіс|кубернетес => Kubernetes
задеплоїти|задеплоїв|задеплоїмо => deploy
хелм чарт => helm chart
